<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,564,1131]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">
<treatmentCitationGroup pageId="4" pageNumber="48">
<treatmentCitation author="Vvedensky, A. I." box="[151,650,564,590]" page=")" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" year="1952">
<taxonomicName authority="Vvedensky (1952: 28)" authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityPageNumber="28" authorityYear="1952" box="[151,650,564,590]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="circumplexa">
<emphasis box="[151,381,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Gagea circumplexa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vvedensky, A. I." box="[388,650,564,590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="28" refId="ref11102" refString="Vvedensky, A. I. (1952) Liliaceae Novae Kirghizicae. Botaniceskie Materialy Gerbarija Instituta Botaniki Akademii Nauk Uzbekskoi SSSR 13: 28." type="journal article" year="1952">Vvedensky (1952: 28)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
and 
<treatmentCitation author="Chodat, R. &amp; Beauverd, J." box="[708,1184,564,590]" page=")" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" year="1932">
<taxonomicName authority="Chodat &amp; Beauverd (1932: 8)" authorityName="Chodat &amp; Beauverd" authorityPageNumber="8" authorityYear="1932" box="[708,1184,564,590]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dayana">
<emphasis box="[708,826,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. dayana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chodat, R. &amp; Beauverd, J." box="[833,1184,564,590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="1932 - 4" refId="ref8818" refString="Chodat, R. H &amp; Beauverd, J. (1932) Gagea dayana, p. 8, in: Dinsmore, J. E. (1932 - 4). Plantae Postianae et Dinsmoreanae, Publications of the American University of Beirut, Natural Science series, Vols. 1. &amp; 2." type="journal article" year="1932">Chodat &amp; Beauverd (1932: 8)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
were the two species of this section included in analyses of molecular data (nrITS and plastid) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1069,1301,602,628]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1149,1210,602,627]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
. These two species grouped with other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schultes &amp; Schultes" authorityYear="1829" baseAuthorityName="Pall." box="[663,808,641,666]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis box="[663,808,641,666]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex in 
<emphasis box="[955,980,641,666]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[1047,1216,641,666]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1047,1216,641,666]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Platyspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(clade C, Figure 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[184,409,680,706]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[269,332,680,705]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). They fell in different subclades in clade C. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityYear="1952" box="[980,1222,680,705]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="circumplexa">
<emphasis box="[980,1222,680,705]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Gagea circumplexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was included by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[151,415,718,744]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[264,326,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
and was placed within their clade A (
<emphasis box="[884,909,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[981,1155,719,744]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[981,1155,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Platyspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). No species from this section were included in anatomical studies, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityYear="1952" box="[723,899,757,782]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="circumplexa">
<emphasis box="[723,899,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. circumplexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was included in palynological studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S." pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="96 - 108" refId="ref11268" refString="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S. (2005) Pollen morphology of the genus Gagea (Liliaceae) in Iran. Flora 200: 96 - 108." type="journal article" year="2005">Zarrei &amp; Zarre 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Based on palynomorphological data, the separate placement of this species is not supported. This section should also be included 
<emphasis box="[584,609,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[676,887,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[676,845,834,859]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="lato">Platyspermum</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[852,887,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,564,1131]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">
In summary, all taxa of clade C should be redefined as 
<emphasis box="[921,949,873,898]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1028,1204,873,898]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[1028,1200,873,898]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Platyspermum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
including 
<emphasis box="[1344,1369,873,898]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="Levichev (1990: 231)" authorityName="Levichev" authorityPageNumber="231" authorityYear="1990" box="[151,661,912,938]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sensu">
<emphasis box="[151,394,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Platyspermum sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Levichev, I. G." box="[402,661,912,938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="225 - 234" refId="ref9564" refString="Levichev, I. G. (1990) The synopsis of the genus Gagea (Liliaceae) from the western Tien-Shan. (in Russian). Botanicheskii Zhurnal 75: 225 - 234." type="journal article" year="1990">Levichev (1990: 231)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[674,699,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[768,902,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Incrustatae</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[918,943,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1012,1179,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Graminifoliae</emphasis>
and probably 
<emphasis box="[1350,1378,912,937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[151,279,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Bulbiferae</emphasis>
. An umbellate inflorescence, flattened seeds, a fairly trilobed stigma, as well as a reticulate to fibrous-reticulate bulb tunic are all putative synapomorphies for this section. Although most species of this section possess a pentangular outline in transverse sections of basal leaves, collenchyma under epidermis, and sclerenchymatous tissues, these are not shared by all taxa. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zarrei &amp; Wilkin (2010 b: 90)" authorityName="Zarrei &amp; Wilkin" authorityPageNumber="90" authorityYear="2010" box="[838,1373,1066,1092]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calcicola">
<emphasis box="[838,1031,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Gagea calcicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1039,1373,1066,1092]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="89 - 96" refId="ref11505" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2010 b) Gagea calcicola (Liliaceae), a new species from southwestern Iran. Kew Bulletin 65: 89 - 96." type="journal article" year="2010">Zarrei &amp; Wilkin (2010b: 90)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is an example of a species in this section with atypical anatomical characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1000,1224,1105,1131]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="89 - 96" refId="ref11505" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2010 b) Gagea calcicola (Liliaceae), a new species from southwestern Iran. Kew Bulletin 65: 89 - 96." type="journal article" year="2010">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1082,1140,1105,1130]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2010b
</bibRefCitation>
, d).
</paragraph>
